pullRequest.title: Chores: bump up f8 dep
pullRequest.bodyText:
Signed-off-by: Stanislav Knot sknot@redhat.com
Type of change

Bugfix
Enhancement

Description
Upgrade fabric8 dependency.
Memory resource changes in tests: It seems getting getSizeLimit().getAmount() was fixed in fabric8 because it was returning (e.g.) 4Gi. It is obvious the amount is 4 (not 4Gi as before, Gi is the format (getSizeLimit().getFormat()).
The bug with detecting java and enabling http2 has been fixed.
I had to do some changes (random resource name) in ITs because of caching resources which caused some flakiness.
Checklist

 Update/write design documentation in ./design
 Write tests
 Make sure all tests pass
 Update documentation
 Check RBAC rights for Kubernetes / OpenShift roles
 Try your changes from Pod inside your Kubernetes and OpenShift cluster, not just locally
 Reference relevant issue(s) and close them after merging
 Update CHANGELOG.md

Have you double checked that the gracePeriod is still maintained from the pod when the withGracePeriod is removed?
This doesn't sound right to me. Why is this needed nd why is this ok to change it?
Again, this does not seem to be right. How does this impact the behaviour of the public APIs where you use 4Gi today?
AFAIK this should be optional or provided to not mix into the runtime binaries.
